The first two-thirds of the slit can therefore be divided into two halves which have a λ/2 path difference.", "fibs": ["slit"]}
{"text": "The contributions of these two halves cancel in the same manner as described earlier.", "fibs": ["manner"]}
{"text": "Only the remaining one-third of the slit contributes to the intensity at a point between the two minima.", "fibs": ["one-third"]}
{"text": "Clearly, this will be much weaker than the central maximum (where the entire slit contributes in phase).", "fibs": ["slit"]}
{"text": "One can similarly show that there are maxima at (n + 1/2) λ/a with n = 2, 3, etc.", "fibs": ["show"]}
